body:
@FlorisHoogenboom thank you for filing this issue. I am having trouble reproducing when using a Databricks backend. Would you mind providing the following:

a) Version of mlflow specified in your project's `conda.yaml`.
b) [Databricks runtime version](https://docs.databricks.com/release-notes/runtime/releases.html) (eg "Databricks Runtime 7.5 for ML")

@AveshCSingh . Thank you for looking into this. We we're running still on 6.6-ml (needing to upgrade to 7.3-ml-lts). As it turns out the issue only exists when running on 6.6-ml and not on 7.3-ml. I've created a small repo for you to reproduce. 

See [here](https://github.com/FlorisHoogenboom/mlflow-double-runs/tree/master) to reproduce the issue on 6.6-ml. See here to run the same project on [7.3-ml-lts ](https://github.com/FlorisHoogenboom/mlflow-double-runs/tree/dbr7.3)(which does not create double runs). Both use `mlflow=1.12.1` in their `environment.yaml` file ([here](https://github.com/FlorisHoogenboom/mlflow-double-runs/blob/4ed0cae5a04579441d1a037d7e44343cafe16260/mlflow-environment.yml#L8)).

It is interesting to see it does not appear on `7.3-ml`. To me that seems to point how that local backend config is interpreted on the backend.
